# Convert to Eastern time
lebron_tweets <- lebron_tweets %>%
  mutate(hour=hour(with_tz(created_at, tz="America/New_York")))

#Set column names
data_cols <- c('created_at', 'display_text_width', 'is_retweet', 'favorite_count', 'retweet_count', 'hashtags', 'media_type', 'mentions_screen_name')

#create a new data set that is filtered and cleaned for appropriate data
data_clean = lebron_tweets[, data_cols]

#Use ggplot to filter and clean data
data_clean = data_clean %>%
  filter(is_retweet == 'FALSE')%>%
  mutate(hashtags_count = ifelse(is.na(hashtags), 0, lengths(hashtags)))%>%
  mutate(media_included = ifelse(is.na(media_type), 0, lengths(media_type)))%>%
  mutate(tag_count = ifelse(is.na(mentions_screen_name), 0, lengths(mentions_screen_name)))%>%
  mutate(day_of_week = weekdays(as.POSIXct(created_at), abbreviate = F))%>%
  mutate(created_at = as.Date(created_at, "%m/%d/%Y"))
